https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/zmgsaKFWbmZ1Grz4SO0PLNxilv3.jpg All Eyez on Me chronicles the life and legacy of Tupac Shakur, including his rise to superstardom as a hip-hop artist, actor, poet and activist, as well as his imprisonment and prolific, controversial time at Death Row Records. Against insurmountable odds, Tupac rose to become a cultural icon whose career and persona both continue to grow long after his passing. All Eyez on Me
